A memorial ceremony will be held Monday at Stockton's Civic Auditorium for the five  children gunned down Tuesday at Cleveland Elementary School by Patrick Edward  Purdy, who then killed himself.
Californians will observe five minutes of silence.
Fourteen of the 30 injured remain in hospitals.
Victims' families are receiving financial  aid from the county victim/witness assistance program.
Buddhist monks led prayers  Friday as part of 3-day mourning ceremonies at the homes of Cambodian families who  lost children.
One father attended from Ohio after learning of his son's death on TV.
His  wife claims she thought he was dead.
Governor Deukmejian is considering a ban on  assault weapon sales. 
